abstract: >-
  hotSpring reproduces published computational plasma physics from the
  Murillo Group (Michigan State University) on consumer hardware, validates
  correctness against reference data (86/86 quantitative checks pass), and
  re-executes computations using BarraCUDA â€” a Pure Rust scientific computing
  library with WGSL GPU shaders. The study covers molecular dynamics (Sarkas),
  plasma equilibration (Two-Temperature Model), and nuclear equation of state
  surrogate learning (Diaw et al., Nature Machine Intelligence 2024). GPU FP64
  validated to 4.55e-13 MeV precision. Energy profiling shows 44.8x less
  energy on GPU vs Python for identical physics.
